    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>EXODUS TO BUY GLOBAL CROSSING UNIT</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Simon Romero</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Romero, Simon</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Exodus Communications will buy Global Crossing's Web-operating unit for about $6.53 billion in stock; deal shows increased emphasis in telecommunications industry on running Web sites (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Exodus Communications confirmed yesterday that it would buy Global Crossing's Web-operating unit for about $6.53 billion in stock. The deal shows the increased emphasis in the telecommunications industry on running Web sites, a business that is growing faster than traditional telecommunications services.</p>
        <p>Simon Romero (NYT)</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
